!! What it does

The cytoscape engine plugin provides an alternative rendering backend for [[tw-graph|$:/plugins/flibbles/graph]]. It replaces vis-network with [[Cytoscape.js|https://js.cytoscape.org/]] (v3.33.2) while keeping the same `<$graph>` widget API — all existing graph markup works unchanged.

!! Key differentiator

''Compound/container nodes'' — Cytoscape.js natively supports grouping nodes inside a visual container via the `cluster` attribute. vis-network has no equivalent.

```
<$graph>
  <$node $tiddler="Team" label="Team Alpha"/>
  <$node $tiddler="Person1" label="Alice" cluster="Team"/>
  <$node $tiddler="Person2" label="Bob" cluster="Team"/>
</$graph>
```

!! What's included

* Full `graphengine` module adapter implementing tw-graph's engine interface
* 10 property handlers: events, positions, nodes, edges, colors, layout, physics, interaction, defaults, IDs
* Cytoscape.js 3.33.2 UMD build as a TiddlyWiki library module
* COSE layout (Compound Spring Embedder) — physics simulation that handles compound nodes natively
* Blur debouncing for stable popup interaction

!! Prerequisites

* `$:/plugins/flibbles/graph` (tw-graph) v1.6.0+
* TiddlyWiki 5.3.0+

